definition: (used for transliteration)/old variant of 謳|讴[ou1]

sentences.english: Inspired by the picture of a valkyrie I found on the internet.
sentences.chinese: 从网路上找到的北欧战神使女的图片得到的灵感。

sentences.english: Well armed and equipped Norse swordsmen. Able to wear chain and plate armour.
sentences.chinese: 北欧剑士装备极为精良，身穿链甲或板甲。

sentences.english: Because, we Swedes, without herrings , we, Scandinavian country, we couldn't live.
sentences.chinese: 瑞典人和北欧人没有鲱鱼即无法存活至今。

sentences.english: My favorite piece of furniture in the whole house is the mid-century Scandinavian sideboard.
sentences.chinese: 整座屋子里我最喜欢的家具就是这个中世纪北欧边桌。

sentences.english: The dreaded wood-eating shipworm is invading northern Europe's Baltic Sea.
sentences.chinese: 可怕的吃木头的船蛆正在侵袭北欧的波罗的海。

sentences.english: The Viking warship replica, Havhingsten af Glendalough (the Sea Stallion of Glendalough), makes its way from Dublin Bay into Dublin Port, Ireland August 14, 2007 .
sentences.chinese: 北欧海盗船复制品从爱尔兰柏林湾航行到柏林港口。

sentences.english: Snus sales and volumes grew in all Scandinavian markets.
sentences.chinese: 在所有的北欧市场中，鼻烟销售额和销量都增长。

sentences.english: My username is the name of a prophetess in Norse mythology.
sentences.chinese: 我的用户名是名称的先知在北欧神话。

sentences.english: The Nordic birches have long been of special interest.
sentences.chinese: 北欧的桦树很久以来就特别引人注目。

sentences.english: The Vikings raped and pillaged all along the coast.
sentences.chinese: 北欧海盗沿着海岸大肆奸淫劫掠。

sentences.english: Nokia is an outsized part of the small Nordic country's economy -and self-image.
sentences.chinese: 诺基亚公司在这个北欧小国经济体中显得异常庞大。

sentences.english: The original population of Iceland was of Nordic and Celtic origin.
sentences.chinese: 冰岛的人口起源北欧人和凯尔特人。

sentences.english: Only Scandinavians have won gold medals in the men's winter Olympics.
sentences.chinese: 只有北欧人获得了冬运会男子越野滑雪项目中的金牌。

sentences.english: Denmark is the smallest and southernmost Nordic country.
sentences.chinese: 丹麦是最小的也是最南端的北欧国家。

sentences.english: ASSE is the American Scandinavian Student Exchange.
sentences.chinese: ASSE是美国北欧学生交流项目。

sentences.english: Protected by mail armour and wielding axes, these fearsome warriors are effective cavalry.
sentences.chinese: 北欧战斧骑兵身穿链甲挥舞利斧，极为骁勇善战。
